Diorite mace-head, chipped under head of body. [drawing]
U is a predyn. cemet. near Umm il Qa 'Ã¢b
See cemet. Abydos II.
SEE OVER

[Plan]
Head direct south, remains in a rectangular space & rising a little to north. Mat over head still visible, no signs of coffin. Body completely disarticulated. Femora are with head north the other head south. Hip bones as figured are over the other & out of position. Coccyx & sacrum over one femur, some ribs & one large ankle bone over breast. Lower jaw attached to head but rather out of position. See Photo.
